&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Role&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic AI Tools Intern to leverage cutting-edge technologies like Gemini, Notebook LM, and Cloudflare Workers. What we hire for isn&#39;t a specific degree. It&#39;s a mindset: curious, technically sharp, and motivated by helping others succeed. This role will focus on enhancing content creation, conducting research, template creation, and updating our internal wiki page. You will gain valuable experience in utilizing AI tools to streamline processes and improve efficiency.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;In a typical week, you might:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and test an AI agent or internal chatbot to help Sales teams work faster, built on Cloudflare Workers AI and AI Gateway&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and prototype a demo that shows Cloudflare&#39;s AI platform capabilities for a real customer use case&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write scripts or lightweight tools that cut manual work out of Go-To-Market workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dig into usage or productivity data to see what impact the tools your team built are actually having&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Present your work at a team showcase or sprint review&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What Success Looks Like&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ship at least one internal AI tool that Solutions Engineering or Go-To-Market colleagues are actively using&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to tools or demos that make a real difference to how the team works&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leave with at least one piece of work the wider team can pick up and use&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;It is critical that you:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Can write working code in Python, JavaScript, or a similar language and ship things independently&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have a basic understanding of how the web works: HTTP, REST APIs, DNS, TLS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Can explain what you built and why, to a technical or non-technical audience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are curious and self-directed. You try things before asking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;It would be awesome if you also:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have played around with LLMs, AI APIs, or prompt engineering, even just in side projects, coursework, or a hackathon&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have used any part of the Cloudflare developer platform: Workers, R2, Pages, or anything similar&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have experience with data analysis or lightweight dashboarding (Python, notebooks, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have shipped something as part of a team: a university capstone, hackathon project, open source contribution, or a previous internship&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Technologies we work with&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cloudflare Workers, Workers AI, AI Gateway, Vectorize, Pages, R2, D1, KV · Python · JavaScript / TypeScript&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Skills/Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;re probably finishing a &lt;strong&gt;degree, or close to it, in computer science, software engineering, data science, or something in that space.&lt;/strong&gt; But your best work probably didn&#39;t happen in a lecture theatre. It happened when you stayed up debugging a side project, shipped something at a hackathon, or found yourself reading documentation for a technology you had no real reason to know yet.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We&#39;re looking for &lt;strong&gt;curious and ambitious builders&lt;/strong&gt; who want to explore a career that mixes technical depth with helping others do their best work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Curious what the programme looks like in practice? &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://blog.cloudflare.com/tag/internship-experience/&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Hear directly from our past interns.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ability to commit to a minimum 12 week summer internship from May to August 2026.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
